# How to import newsletter subscribers from LibCal into Mailchimp
1. Navigate to the LibCal Homepage (https://libcal.library.ubc.ca/admin/home).
2. Click on "Event Calendars" at the top of the page.
3. Click on "Event Explorer" to the right of "UBC Vancouver Library Public Events".
4. Select the date range in the "From" and "To" fields for workshops you would like to include.
5. Select "UBC Library Research Commons Workshops Registration Form" in the "Booking Form" field.
6. Select "Research Commons" in the "Category" field.
7. Click on "Submit". Any Research Common's workshop held during this time period will appear below.
8. Click on "Export Data".
9. Open the downloaded CSV file.
10. Delete all columns except:
"First Name"
"Last Name"
"Email"
"Choose your Faculty or Unit from the drop-down."
"Would you like to receive the UBC Library Research Commons Monthly newsletter (of current offerings and news) at the email address you provided above?"
11. Rename the "Email" column to "Email Address" and the "Choose your Faculty or Unit from the drop-down." column to "Faculty".
12. Move the "Email Address" column so that it is the first column in the series.
13. Sort the data by the "Would you like to receive the UBC Library Research Commons Monthly newsletter..." column in descending order. ("Yes" responses should be on top.)

![](../../assets/images/filter_popup.png)

14. Select and copy all the data to the left of a "Yes" reply.
12. Login to Mailchimp (https://mailchimp.com/). See documentation for username and password.
12. On the right-hand side of the Audience page, click on "View Contacts".
13. Click on "Add contacts", then "Import contacts".
14. On the Where do you want to import contacts from? page, select "Copy/paste from file".
15. Click "Continue" in the lower right-hand corner of the page.
16. Paste the data into the "Paste contact info" box.
17. Click the "I understand that my billing plan may be automatically upgraded." box.
18. Click "Continue To Match" in the lower right-hand corner of the screen.
19. You should see "All columns are matched" on the "Import contacts" screen. Click "Continue To Organize" in the lower right-hand corner.
20. On the "Organize your imported contacts" screen, make sure "Subscribed" is selected under "Choose status if these contacts".
21. Select the "Update existing contacts" box.
22. Click "Continue To Review" in the lower right-hand corner of the screen. The following screen should like tlike this:
23. Click "Import" in the lower right-hand corner.

That's it! Your current number of contacts and subscribers will be listed here:
